# Go style

## Lint and static analysis

- `go vet ./...` clean on every PR.
- `staticcheck ./...` clean on every PR.
- `gosec ./...` clean for `internal/secrets/`, `internal/uploader/`, `internal/runner/`. Findings in those packages are PR blockers unless explicitly waived in review.

## Style

- No mutable package globals. Pass config and context through constructors.
- Wrap errors with `fmt.Errorf("...: %w", err)`; never `%v` for an error you intend to expose.
- Subprocess invocation uses `exec.CommandContext`, never `exec.Command`, so timeouts and cancels actually take effect.
- Goroutines that read pipes own a `done` channel; the runner's cleanup waits on it. No goroutines spawned inside a screen's `Update`.

## Tests

- Drive screens by calling `Update` directly with synthetic messages.
- Snapshot renders with `github.com/bradleyjkemp/cupaloy` at fixed sizes (80x24 and 200x60).
- Mock runner replays recorded fixtures from `testdata/recorded/<EVD-*>.{stdout,json}` so CI is deterministic without AWS / Paramify creds.

## Two-approval areas

PRs touching the following require two approvals:

- `internal/secrets/` — credential handling
- `internal/uploader/` — Paramify API
- `internal/runner/real.go` — subprocess execution (RCE surface)
- Anything that materially changes behavior cited in [DESIGN.md](../../DESIGN.md) Part 3.
